<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-811] updateFirst methods do not increment @Version field</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-811</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When updating one record that is versioned with a &lt;tt&gt;@Version&lt;/tt&gt; annotation, I was expecting the version field to be incremented automatically by the Spring Data layer just as is the behavior of JPA. This however does not happen and I have to add &lt;tt&gt;&#8230;.inc(&quot;version&quot;, 1)&lt;/tt&gt; to the update object in order to get the increment. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure that this is a bug, or my understanding is incorrect. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
